ADM Human Resources 
This is a remote contract position
 
 
 About The Role: 
We are seeking a Contract Recruiter for our Talent Acquisition team in North America. To excel, you'll utilize your recruiting skills to research and network with passive candidates, be a creative problem-solver and establish strong partnerships with hiring managers. It's a fast-paced and dynamic role on an energetic and inclusive team where thinking about things in new ways is strongly supported. You'll also work on strategic projects to improve and innovate how we attract and recruit the best talent, because we know that there's always a better way - from generating a candidate pipeline to exploring artificial intelligence, you'll be one of the go-to individuals when it comes to handling the entire candidate recruitment process for your business/es. We're looking for a creative, driven individual who has strong interpersonal skills and also the ability to create and maintain lasting relationships with both candidates and hiring managers.
 
 
 In This Role You Will: 
Build solid relationships with hiring managers and develop a keen understanding of our internal skill sets and team dynamics 
Act as an ambassador of ADM and help create a strong employer-of-choice brand 
Use your knowledge of the competitive landscape to build recruiting strategies for open positions 
Own the full cycle recruiting process, including sourcing and closing all candidates 
Drive an efficient hiring process and maintain quality pipeline metrics via the ATS (Kenexa/Brassring) 
Job Requirements:
 2+ years‚Äô experience as a full life-cycle recruiter is strongly preferred
 Experience with a temporary agency is highly desirable 
Experience with targeted sourcing strategies to find talent for niche roles or in challenging talent markets. 
Self-motivated with superior organizational skills, integrity and follow through. 
Experience in building sourcing plans for client groups 
You are able to work independently and with little supervision 
Excellent written and verbal communication skills 
Relocation assistance is not available with this position.
 
ADM requires the successful completion of a pre-employment drug screen and a background check.
 
ADM is an EOE for minorities, females, protected veterans and individuals with a disability. 
 
 
